article.headline: Austin Peay 85, SE Missouri 82
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Fernandez Lockett scored 23 and grabbed 13 rebounds to lead Austin Peay to a 85-82 win over Southeast Missouri on Saturday night. Drake Reed also added 23 points for Austin Peay (11-7, 7-1 Ohio Valley), which led by as much as 15 points in the first half. But soon into the second half, Southeast Missouri (11-7, 6-2) started a 13-to-2 run at 15:56 that gave them the lead 60-59. Will Bogan led Southeast Missouri with 17 points and Jaycen Herring and Marcus Rhodes added 13 points each. Austin Peay battled back in the final minutes with solid 3-point shooting, including two by Wes Channels, who finished with 14 points for the game.
